 This site explained a lot for me::

 http://www.hastingsmfg.com/Service%20Tips/valve_spring_inserts.htm

 I have a pair of 2 liter heads from a hydraulic lifter '78 GE engine, and
 onle ONE of the heads had 'valve spring inserts / spacers / seats' .  Now I know why.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

If you have spacers under the springs, a machine shop put them there to beef up weak springs. WHERE he got the
spring specs from, I don't know. Some 'expert' shops put them in just because......
